## M19(5/6): calling an extern function from a safe context is rejected.
##
## Per GPT-5.5 entry 35 (M19 design): "all extern calls require
## unsafe even if the extern declaration is not syntactically
## marked unsafe." Extern declarations are the FFI boundary and
## bypass Rig's ownership / effect contracts. Calling an extern
## from a safe context would silently treat a C/Zig API as
## ownership-safe; the unsafe wrapping requirement forces the
## caller to acknowledge the bargain.

extern puts: fn(String) Int

sub main()
  puts("hi")       # error: extern call requires unsafe context
